\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  dubium} : Upper leaves sessile with cuneate base, rarely shortly petiolate. Petals red, mostly without basal spot. Latex white or cream, black to brown when dry. 2n = 42. {\i Throughout the range of the species}.
