\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  somniferum} (incl. subsp.{\i  hortense} (Hussenot) Corb., subsp.{\i  songaricum }Basil.): Subglabrous, strongly glaucous, usually unbranched. Upper leaves usually little divided. Sepals glabrous. Filaments clavate, pale violet. Capsule often indehiscent. 2n = 22. {\i Cultivated and naturalized throughout most of the range of the species.}
