\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  setigerum} (DC.) Arcangeli, {\i Comp. Fl. Ital.} 25 (1882) ({\i P. setigerum }DC.): With more or less densely setose indumentum, weakly glaucous. Upper leaves usually pinnatifid. Sepals with at least some setae. Filaments filiform or clavate, dark violet. Capsules always dehiscent. 2n = (22), 44.{\i  Mainly W. Mediterranean region, where it is probably native}.
